text:
Very underwhelming, she's not a strong dancer. They should have focused more on her vocals and the ranges that she has instead of making her dance which in comparison to her teammates she's very not skilled. The choreography was clearly made slow, and sharp to fit her awkward moments. She's well hidden when in BlackPink [as a group] but as a solo, u clearly can see her flaws. The dancers seem to HAVE TO match slow and awkward movements, which becomes more noticeable.

The song itself is great and the choreography too. The song for sure fits her voice, but that's all.
